Vegan Pasta Alfredo
  -Iosune

4 oz gf uncooked spaghetti
1 tsp evoo
1 clove garlic, minced
3/4 c unsweetened almond milk
1 c raw cauliflower, chopped
salt a freshly ground black pepper to taste
1 tbsp nutritional yeast
1/2 tbsp lemon juice

Cook pasta al dente per package instructions. Heat oil in a frying pan and cook the garlic over medium high heat for 3-4 min or until golden brown. Add the almond milk and bring to a boil. Lower the heat, add cauliflower, salt, and peper, and cook for ~7 min or until the cauliflower is soft. Transfer to a blender, add the nutritional yeast and lemon juice. Blend until smooth. Drain the pasta and pour it into the pan with the sauce. Stir and serve.

Notes: Can garnish with dried oregano. Can also use regular pasta. To make sauce creamier, add 1 tbsp tahini. For gf pasta, brown rice or buckwheat pasta taste better. 
